# Fuzz corpus + regression seeds are raw byte fixtures (msgpack, arbitrary
# bytes). Mark them binary so git never emits a raw-byte "text" diff for them:
# an unmarked corpus seed without a NUL in its first 8 KiB is treated as text,
# and the resulting non-UTF-8 diff bytes break tools that read `git diff`
# (the diff-scoped mutation-smoke gate, meta-gate, etc.). `binary` => -diff, so
# git prints "Binary files differ" instead.
bpk-lib/fuzz/corpus/** binary
bpk-lib/fuzz/regressions/** binary
